## **1. Product Definition & Requirement Gathering**

### 🔹 User Requirements
- Identify primary users and their roles.  
- Estimate user volume and role-based access.  
- Determine device usage (mobile, desktop, tablet).  
- Assess need for mobile UI or responsive design.  
- Clarify if multiple instances of the app will run.  

### 🔹 Functional Requirements
- Define core product functionalities.  
- List all actions the application should perform.  
- Break down features into modules/screens.  
- Map APIs to screens and estimate round-trip request complexity.  

### 🔹 Technical Requirements
- Number of UI screens and their complexity.  
- Reference existing wireframes or prototypes.  
- Define architecture: monolith vs. microservices.  
- Technology stack: ReactJS (mandatory or flexible?), libraries, frameworks.  
- API authentication mechanism: Password, OAuth, JWT, etc.  
- Backend schema alignment with UI.  
- Device targeting and responsive design strategy.  

### 🔹 Non-Functional Requirements
- Performance expectations.  
- Security standards (OWASP, CORS, SSO).  
- Accessibility compliance.  
- Maintainability and scalability.  

---

## **2. Analysis Phase**

### 🔹 Requirement Analysis
- Validate gathered requirements.  
- Interface analysis: interaction with other systems.  
- Define user stories (Who, What, Why).  
- Categorize RESTful resources (e.g., vehicle/car/purchase).  

### 🔹 Technology Selection
- Choose frontend frameworks (ReactJS, alternatives).  
- Select libraries (ECharts, Bootstrap, etc.).  
- Decide on architecture (MVC, MVP, MVVM).  
- Evaluate microservice feasibility.  

### 🔹 Workflow & Navigation
- Define user journeys and screen transitions.  
- Map navigation logic and screen dependencies.  

---

## **3. Design Phase**

### 🔹 Wireframing & Prototyping
- Create low-fidelity sketches and clickable prototypes.  
- Design branding, appearance, and layout.  
- Define visual hierarchy and UI components.  

### 🔹 Design Specifications
- Document design standards and UI guidelines.  
- Ensure consistency across screens and devices.  

---

## **4. User Experience (UX) Design**

### 🔹 High-Level UX Design
- Illustrate user behavior and interaction flows.  
- Identify key touchpoints and feedback mechanisms.  
- Validate UX with stakeholders using prototypes.  

---

## **5. Development Phase**

### 🔹 Frontend Development
- Build UI using ReactJS, Bootstrap, ECharts.  
- Implement reusable components and layouts.  
- Integrate APIs and handle request/response logic.  

### 🔹 Coding Standards & Practices
- Frequent commits with meaningful messages.  
- Use ESLint, Husky for code quality.  
- Apply BEM methodology for CSS.  
- Separate dev and prod dependencies.  
- Use CSS preprocessors (SASS/LESS).  
- Optimize performance and memory usage.  
- Follow accessibility and security standards.  

### 🔹 Architecture & Tools
- Use Gulp/Webpack for bundling.  
- Apply design patterns (MVC, MVVM).  
- Manage dependencies and enable tree shaking.  
- Handle CORS, SSO, and OWASP compliance.  

---

## **6. Validation & Testing**

### 🔹 Testing & Debugging
- Perform UI testing and integration testing.  
- Use Jasmine/Karma for unit tests.  
- Debug using browser DevTools and console.  
- Conduct linting (ES6) and static code analysis (Sonar/Checkmarx).  

### 🔹 Quality Assurance
- Validate performance tuning.  
- Check for memory leaks.  
- Ensure compliance with coding standards.  

---

## **7. Deployment & Delivery**

### 🔹 Build & Deployment
- Prepare builds (standard or Docker-based).  
- Deploy to staging/production environments.  
- Monitor application health and performance.  

### 🔹 Post-Deployment Support
- Provide integration support.  
- Maintain version control and rollback strategies.  
- Plan for future enhancements and scalability.  

